  "texts": [
    "The delayed kinetics of PCNA-mono-ubiquitination suggest that TMZ-induced RAD18 activation requires a second round of DNA synthesis.",
    "Indeed, the number of cells actively synthesizing DNA was not significantly affected during the first 24 h of TMZtreatment (Fig. 1e).",
    "However, 48 h post-TMZ treatment, we observed accumulation of BrdU-positive cells with late-S/G2 DNA content (Fig. 1e).",
    "Supplementary Fig. 1 shows that in nocodazole-synchronized cells PCNA mono-ubiquitination peaks in the second cell cycle following TMZ treatment.",
    "Critically, nocodazole treatment to block passage into a second cell cycle abrogated the TMZ-induced PCNA mono-ubiquitination."
